The paper focuses on visual kinship recognition and proposes a two-stage kin-face generation model using deep generative adversarial autoencoder and DNA-Net. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image generation and recognition, as well as machine learning (ML) techniques such as deep learning and generative models. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves AI techniques such as generative models and neural networks, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. The paper also involves graphics (GR) techniques such as image rendering and manipulation, which makes cs.GR (Graphics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves multimedia (MM) techniques such as image and video processing, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
